msgstr "Accountant"

msgid "Accountant Job Duties: Prepares asset, liability, and capital account entries by compiling and analyzing account information. Documents financial transactions by entering account information. Recommends financial actions by analyzing accounting options. Summarizes current financial status by collecting information; preparing balance sheet, profit and loss statement, and other reports. Substantiates financial transactions by auditing documents. Maintains accounting controls by preparing and recommending policies and procedures. Guides accounting clerical staff by coordinating activities and answering questions. Reconciles financial discrepancies by collecting and analyzing account information. Secures financial information by completing data base backups. Maintains financial security by following internal controls. Prepares payments by verifying documentation, and requesting disbursements. Answers accounting procedure questions by researching and interpreting accounting policy and regulations. Complies with federal, state, and local financial legal requirements by studying existing and new legislation, enforcing adherence to requirements, and advising management on needed actions. Prepares special financial reports by collecting, analyzing, and summarizing account information and trends. Maintains customer confidence and protects operations by keeping financial information confidential. Maintains professional and technical knowledge by attending educational workshops; reviewing professional publications; establishing personal networks; participating in professional societies. Accomplishes the result by performing the duty. Contributes to team effort by accomplishing related results as needed."
msgstr "Accountant Job Duties: Prepares asset, liability, at capital account entries ng compiling at analyzing account information. Documents financial transactions ng entering account information. Recommends financial actions ng analyzing accounting mga opsyon. Summarizes current financial status ng collecting information; preparing balance sheet, profit at loss statement, at other mga ulat. Substantiates financial transactions ng auditing documents. Maintains accounting controls ng preparing at recommending policies at procedures. Guides accounting clerical staff ng coordinating activities at answering questions. Reconciles financial discrepancies ng collecting at analyzing account information. Secures financial information ng completing data base backups. Maintains financial security ng following internal controls. Prepares mga pagbabayad ng verifying documentation, at requesting disbursements. Answers accounting procedure questions ng researching at interpreting accounting policy at regulations. Complies gamit ang federal, estado, at local financial legal requirements ng studying kasalukuyang at bago legislation, enforcing adherence sa requirements, at advising management sa needed actions. Prepares special financial mga ulat ng collecting, analyzing, at summarizing account information at trends. Maintains customer confidence at protects operations ng keeping financial information confidential. Maintains professional at technical knowledge ng attending educational workshops; reviewing professional publications; establishing personal networks; participating sa professional societies. Accomplishes ang result ng performing ang duty. Contributes sa team effort ng accomplishing kaugnay results bilang needed."

